article.description: Lamar sneaks past Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 66-64
article.headline: Lamar sneaks past Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 66-64
article.linkText: Lamar sneaks past Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 66-64
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- Anthony Holliday made a layup with 5 seconds left and finished with a career-high 25 points to help Lamar sneak past Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 66-64 on Monday night. Bryce Douvier's last second 3-point attempt was off the mark for Texas A&M-Corpus Christi. Holliday nailed a 3-pointer to give Lamar a 63-59 lead with 1:57 remaining. Douvier answered with a 3 and Holliday then split a pair of free throws for a 64-62 advantage with 1:04 left. Brandon Pye hit a jumper to tie but then Holliday drove in for the winning layup. Holliday, who was 3 of 4 from long range, also had eight assists and had 17 points in the second half for Lamar (9-7, 3-1 Southland Conference). Pye made 5 of 8 3-point attempts to total 21 points, Rashwan Thomas had 15 and Douvier added 13 for the Islanders (7-8, 2-1).
